        "subject": "LU-2789 mdt: take lov_mutex in mdt_attr_set to avoid race",
        "message": "LU-2789 mdt: take lov_mutex in mdt_attr_set to avoid race\n\nThere is a race condition between setstripe and chown.  Conditionally\ntaking lov_mutex before calling mo_attr_set avoids this race\ncondition.\nThe lock condition is having the LA_UID or LA_GID flags set, which is\nalways true when doing a chown.\n\nAlso corrected two instances of an incorrect comment\n(unpack_setattr should be mdt_setattr_unpack).\n\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <paf@cray.com>\nChange-Id: Ic7e55a0bff231b8fb28a400aebb8d6bf7df5baea\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
